General Houston arrived in Galveston from Austin, the Congress having closed session for the season - on my introduction to the President, he gave me a friendly welcome to the county. Note III. <start writing marked out> He had been twice called on to be its Chief Magistrate and spoke in the most kind manner of a Gentleman a friend of mine informed me that he had appointed him Counsel General from Texas to Great Britain. I need hardly mention the name of the person in question - but I mean Mr. Wm. Kennedy - he [unclear] arrived from San Antonio having been then to be that part of the county, the Texas Govt. having conceded to have a grant of land of considerable extent in that quarter - for the introduction of European Immigrants under certain stipulations. <end writing marked out>
